The paper deals with the problem of finding high dimensional approximate nearest neighbors, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science such as data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT). The use of sparse features and dimensional reduction also suggests a connection to these sub-categories.
